,"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"susan-brown-1828"},"H03872":{"id":"H03872","former_ids":["HD3223"],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"Thomas","middle_name":"Harvey","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Thomas Harvey Hooker"},"birth":{"year":1840,"month":7,"day":15,"city":"Murray","county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1919,"city":"Stafford","county":"Genesee County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H02424","mother_id":"X02241"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02269","date_year":1863,"date_month":2,"date_day":12,"location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1919,"children_ids":["H05030","H05031"]}],"tags":["cousin_marriage"],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Married third cousin from Myron Hooker line","body":"Thomas Harvey Hooker married Caroline E. 'Carrie' Shader on February 12, 1863. Both spouses were third cousins descending from Captain Thomas Hooker — Thomas Harvey through his father Thomas Edwin Hooker, and Caroline through her mother Laura Electa Hooker Shader whose father Myron Hooker was Thomas Edwin's half-brother. The cousin-marriage united two Hooker descent paths that had separated several generations earlier."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"His cousin marriage merged two separated Hooker lines","body":"Thomas Harvey Hooker's marriage to his third cousin Caroline Shader re-merged two Hooker family lines that had separated three generations earlier through the half-brother split between his father Thomas Edwin and her grandfather Myron. The cousin marriage was a deliberate or coincidental rejoin of two parallel Hooker descent streams in western New York. He and his wife maintained the Hooker surname throughout their marriage."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Eldest son of Thomas Edwin Hooker","body":"Thomas Harvey Hooker was born July 15, 1840 in Murray, Orleans County New York — eldest son of Thomas Edwin Hooker and Lucy Hyde Hooker. The Hooker family had migrated to the western New York lake-plain region during the early nineteenth century along with many other Connecticut Yankees seeking new agricultural land."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Born Orleans County NY, died Stafford NY 1919","body":"Thomas Harvey Hooker died March 21, 1919 in Stafford, Genesee County New York at age seventy-eight. His two children — Lucy and Alvah — both lived into the mid-twentieth century, with Alvah surviving until 1953 and Lucy until 1924."}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM152","plot_notes":"Stafford Rural Cemetery, Stafford Genesee County NY — same plot area as wife Caroline + daughter Alva + son-in-law Jean Mason + infant grandson H. Mason"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"thomas-hooker-1840"},"H03873":{"id":"H03873","former_ids":["HD3224"],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"female","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"Esther","middle_name":"Lucy","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[],"gender":"female","display_name":"Esther Lucy Hooker"},"birth":{"year":1843},"death":{"year":1925},"parents":{"father_id":"H02424","mother_id":"X02241"},"marriages":[],"tags":["new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"esther-hooker-1843"},"H03874":{"id":"H03874","former_ids":["HD3225"],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"female","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"Emma","middle_name":"L.","last_name":"Brockway","maiden_name":"Hooker","married_names":["Brockway"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Emma L. Hooker Brockway"},"birth":{"year":1846,"month":9,"day":3,"city":"Murray","county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1940,"month":2,"day":16,"note":"Died Feb 16, 1940 at about age 93. WikiTree records age \"about 93.\" Location not yet documented in available sources."},"parents":{"father_id":"H02424","mother_id":"X02241"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02275","date_year":1879,"date_month":3,"date_day":30,"location_city":"Murray","location_county":"Orleans County","location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1895,"children_ids":["HD3259"]}],"tags":["extraordinary_longevity","new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Born before the Mexican-American War; died in 1940","body":"Emma Louisa Hooker Brockway was born September 3, 1846 in Murray, Orleans County, New York and died February 16, 1940 at approximately ninety-three — born two years before the Gold Rush and dying seven months after Germany invaded Poland. She married Isaac Wesley Brockway at Murray on March 30, 1879 and lived into a century that her parents, both born in the 1810s in the same upstate New York county, could not have imagined; her lifespan bridged the entire arc from the antebellum frontier to the eve of the Second World War."},{"category":"family","header":"Outlived husband Wesley by forty-five years","body":"Her husband Wesley Brockway — formally Isaac Wesley Brockway, an Erie Canal coal merchant and boatman — died in 1895. Emma outlived him by forty-five years; she also outlived her only son Edwin by about a year, dying February 1940 at approximately ninety-three.","number":2},{"category":"marriage","header":"Inherited husband's three children from first marriage","body":"When she married Wesley Brockway in March 1879 at thirty-two, he was forty-five and a widower with three children (Mabel, Archie, Fred) from his first marriage to Marion Peggs. Emma added one son Edwin in November 1880 — and would later see Edwin name his own first daughter Mabel for her older half-sister.","number":3}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Mount Albion Cemetery, Albion Orleans County NY"},"slug":"emma-brockway-1846"},"H03875":{"id":"H03875","former_ids":["HD3226"],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"female","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker"