:1915,"children_ids":["HD3236","HD3237","HD3238"]}],"tags":["cousin_marriage","new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Married fellow Hooker descendant, third-cousin distance","body":"William Henry 'Willie' Hooker married Lydia Mason Robinson — herself a Hooker descendant via her grandmother Laura E. Hooker Shader, daughter of Captain Thomas Hooker's son Myron Hooker. William Henry and Lydia were third cousins once removed; their marriage united two Hooker-line branches in a single household, with their son Charles Theodore Hooker holding documented double Hooker ancestry through both parents."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Two brothers each married a Shader-line Hooker cousin","body":"The cousin marriage was paralleled in the family: William Henry's brother Thomas Harvey Hooker had also married a Shader-line Hooker cousin (Caroline E. Shader, Lydia's aunt). Two brothers Thomas Edwin Hooker's sons each thus married a Shader-line Hooker woman, making their offspring doubly Hooker-descended on both maternal and paternal sides. The pattern thickened the Hooker-line concentration in the Murray, Orleans County New York branch."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Born Murray NY 1864, three children with Lydia","body":"William Henry Hooker was born August 18, 1864 in Murray, Orleans County New York — the eldest child of Thomas Edwin Hooker by his second wife Susan M. Brown. He died May 15, 1933 in Brockport, Monroe County New York at age sixty-eight, buried at Beach Ridge Cemetery Brockport. He had three children with Lydia: C. Theodore Hooker (1891-1971), Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow (1896-1928 died young at 31), and Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty (1902-1993)."}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Beach Ridge Cemetery, Brockport, Monroe County NY (per Findagrave). Same as wife Lydia Mason Robinson Hooker."},"nickname":"Willie","residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"william-hooker-1864"},"H03881":{"id":"H03881","former_ids":["HD3232"],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"Charles","middle_name":"Edward","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Charles Edward Hooker"},"birth":{"year":1867},"death":{"year":1876,"cause":"died young (age 9)"},"parents":{"father_id":"H02424","mother_id":"X02242"},"marriages":[],"tags":["died_young","new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Charles died young","body":"Charles died in 1876, aged about nine."}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"charles-hooker-1867"},"H03882":{"id":"H03882","former_ids":["HD3233"],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"female","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"Susanna","middle_name":"Stephens","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[],"gender":"female","display_name":"Susanna Stephens Hooker"},"birth":{"year":1868,"month":10,"day":18,"city":"Murray","state":"New York